<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idf68b29c9-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s10321"><num value="10321">§ 10321.</num><heading> General penalty</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="idf68b29ca-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s10321/a"><num value="a">(a)</num><content> A person violating any provision of this chapter or a regulation prescribed under this chapter is liable to the United States Government for a civil penalty of not more than $5,000.</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="idf68b29cb-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s10321/b"><num value="b">(b)</num><content> The vessel is liable in rem for any penalty assessed under this section.</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="idf68b29cc-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5">(<ref href="/us/pl/98/89">Pub. L. 98–89</ref>, <date date="1983-08-26">Aug. 26, 1983</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/97/569">97 Stat. 569</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/103/206/tIV/s412">Pub. L. 103–206, title IV, § 412</ref>, <date date="1993-12-20">Dec. 20, 1993</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/107/2437">107 Stat. 2437</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
